[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          the $1,847 while the appeal is happening?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Bot:     I'm a chatbot and can't give you a binding
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          answer on payment timing during the appeal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          Generally, under No Surprises Act
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          protections, you don't have to pay more
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          than the in-network cost-share while a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          dispute is in progress, but the specifics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          of your situation depend on the appeal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          outcome and on the provider's billing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          practices.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          I'm flagging your question for the appeals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          agent who calls you tomorrow so they can
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          give you a clear answer. In the meantime,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          here's a tip: many plans recommend that
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          you not pay the disputed amount until the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          appeal is resolved, but you should follow
